ocal sweets (\u20b980).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Day\u202f2 \u2013 Culture & Departure\\n- **Early Breakfast** (included for mid & luxury; budget: local tea\u2011snack \u2013\u202f\u20b950).\\n- **Morning**\\n  - **Kalyana Pasupatheeswarar Temple** (if missed details) or **Kaveri Boat Ride** (\u20b9200 per person) for sunrise views.\\n- **Mid\u2011morning**\\n  - Check\u2011out and store luggage at hotel reception.\\n  - Visit **Kalyana Pasupatheeswarar\u2019s nearby **Mariamman Temple** (free) and shop for **hand\u2011loom fabrics** (budget\u202f\u2248\u202f\u20b9500\u2011\u20b91,000).\\n- **Lunch**\\n  - *Hotel Sree Krishna* \u2013 vegetarian thali \u2013 **\u20b9220\u202f/\u202fperson**.\\n- **Afternoon**\\n  - Return to Karur railway station via auto\u2011rickshaw (\u20b9150) and board the **return train** to Chennai (same fare as inbound).\\n- **Evening**\\n  - Arrive home; total travel time \u2248\u202f6\u202fhrs.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Approximate Cost Breakdown (per person)\\n\\n| Item | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\\n|------|------------|--------------|------------|\\n| Train (round\u2011trip, AC 2\u2011tier) | 1,600 | 1,600 | 1,600 |\\n| Local transport (autos, rickshaws) | 500 | 500 | 500 |\\n| Accommodation (1 night) | 1,200 | 2,500 | 5,500 |\\n| Meals (2 breakfasts, 2 lunches, 2 dinners) | 1,200 | 1,800 | 2,800 |\\n| Activities & entry fees | 300 | 300 | 300 |\\n| Souvenirs / shopping | 800 | 1,200 | 2,000 |\\n| **Total Approx.** | **5,600** | **7,900** | **12,700** |\\n\\nEven with the luxury option, the total stays well under the **\u20b950,000** ceiling, leaving ample room for extra meals, additional shopping, or an upgrade to a higher\u2011class train (e.g., AC\u202f1\u2011tier \u2248\u202f\u20b92,500 round\u2011trip) while still staying comfortably within budget.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Quick Tips\\n- **Book train tickets** 2\u20133 weeks in advance via IRCTC to secure AC 2\u2011tier seats.\\n- **Carry cash** for small vendors; most local shops accept only cash.\\n- **Dress modestly** when visiting temples (shoulders and knees covered).\\n- **Stay hydrated** \u2013 carry a reusable water bottle; refill at hotels.\\n\\nEnjoy a relaxed cultural immersion in Mayanoor, Karur!  \\n\\nAPPROVE.\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_37a13b2d-f94f-4b9e-bd58-0cef842291b7/37a13b2d-f94f-4b9e-bd58-0cef842291b7", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
